<section class="container-grid sections" id="section-3">
    <div class="grid-content">
        <section>
            <img src="img/HTML5-logo.svg" alt="html 5 logo">
            <h1 class="section-title">Document Type</h1>
            <p>The declaration must be the very first thing in your HTML document, before the &lt;html&gt; tag. Notice how much cleaner the html 5 doctype is vs. the html 4.</p>

            <article>
                <h3>HTML 5 DOCTYPE</h3>
                <p>Please note we will always use HTML 5 docs for this class and all future web classes.</p>
                <p>&lt;!DOCTYPE html&gt;</p>
            </article>

            <article>
                <h3>HTML 4 DOCTYPE</h3>
                <p>&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.01 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/html4/loose.dtd&gt;</p>
            </article>
            
        </section>
    </div>
</section>